         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">73 Chancery Lane ¶ 13 Septr 84 ¶ My dear Mr Berry ¶  ¶ I have long been striving to have a "Key" to the Botany of Victoria published as I know from experience what facilities such a work affords to be...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M84.09.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Stanley Dobson to Graham Berry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A84/8354, unit 59, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also S. Dobson to J. Service, 12 September 1884 (in this edition as M84-09-12).</p>
               </note>73 Chancery Lane</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">13 Septr 84</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mr Berry</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have long been striving to have a "Key" to the Botany of Victoria published as I know from experience what facilities such a work affords to beginners. I have at last induced the Baron v. Müller to take up the idea and he writes me<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> that he has applied to you offically for the necessary permission.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to G. Berry, 11 September 1884 (in this edition as 84-09-11a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am either at this moment or I shall be in a week or two, a Fellow of the Linnean Society of London which I mention simply to show you that I know what I am writing about.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A "Key" to the Tasmainian Flora was published some years ago by the late Revd W. W. Spicer,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Spicer (1878).</p>
               </note> and it is difficult to describe what an impulse the appearance of this small work gave to the study of Botanical Science in the neighbouring Colony.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As this work cannot be done withough increasing the Baron's vote may I hope that you will approve of it<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also, in the same file, S. Dobson to E. Thomas, 17 September 1884.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yrs very faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Stanley Dobson</p>
         </div>
